Xpath:
1) Absolute Xpath:
Reasons why its not recommended:
- the path may change if any changes are made in the document
- its too long
- E.g. Facebook.com -> /html/body/div/div/div/div/div/div/div[2]/div/div/form/div/div/input

Syntax: html/body/p
<html>
  <body>
   <input>
    <p>hello</p>*
  </body>
</html>

2) Relative Xpath

Syntax:
- Attribute - //tagname[@attribute='value']

- Text - //tagname[text()='value']

- Contains method:
//tagname[contains(@attribute,'value')]
//tagname[contains(text(),'value')]

- Starts-with method:
//tagname[starts-with(@attribute,'value')]
//tagname[starts-with(text(),'value')]

